      <div class="ians-column">

        <h2>Understanding your learner population</h2>

        <p>For a student to thrive, it is essential that an environment and culture of <strong>openness and positivity</strong> towards <strong>learning and safety</strong> exists.  Learning will be more effective in an environment where everyone feels comfortable about discussing <strong>mistakes</strong>, as well as the <strong>quality</strong> of each other's work, without invoking <strong>blame</strong> or shame.</p>

        <p>Imagine the detrimental consequences and effect on learning for everybody at an ATC Unit where people don't communicate or, more subtly, only communicate about certain things!</p>

      </div>

      <div class="oj-lowlight oj-hero oj-hero-head-in-hands"></div>

      <div class="ians-column">

        <p>As instructors, we play a vital part in encouraging and creating an optimal learning environment for your students.</p>

        <p>This environment is created by the behaviours and attitudes of the people working there and it is vital that a <strong>culture</strong> exists where learning is actively encouraged and facilitated. </p>

        <p>Unit management also plays a key role in the formation of the workplace culture. In a safe and positive environment, <strong>sharing and reporting</strong> of information about mistakes, incidents and occurrences is shared without fear. </p>

        <p>In a positive environment the student is quickly made to feel a part of a team.</p>

        <p>A poor workplace culture will <strong>prevent</strong> the students from asking the questions that will help them to learn.  They will feel reluctant to report their own and the mistakes of others.  This, in turn, will create a situation which will impact on safety and will ultimately create an air of <strong>learning stagnation</strong> at the unit.</p>

        <p>In an ATC operational environment, there are many different circumstances where some form of training is
                needed and likewise, the people who need this training may have very different <strong>learning profiles</strong>. Bear
                in mind that each person brings with them a particular approach to learning and their expectations of
                the support they will receive from the instructors.</p>
      </div>

